sources.description:
Beyond Tomorrow (also known as And So Goodbye and Beyond Christmas) is a 1940 American fantasy film directed by A. Edward Sutherland and produced by noted cinematographer Lee Garmes

B&W version: https://youtu.be/80cbk1E1wbE

Summary:
Three engineers forge meaningful connections on Christmas Eve, but after their untimely deaths, their spirits intervene to guide a young couple toward love, redemption, and a second chance at life.

Main Actors: 
Harry Carey - George Melton
C. Aubrey Smith - Allan Chadwick
Charles Winninger - Michael O'Brien
Alex Melesh - Josef the butler
Maria Ouspenskaya - Madam Tanya
Helen Vinson - Arlene Terry
Rod La Rocque - Phil Hubert
Richard Carlson - James Houston
Jean Parker - Jean Lawrence
J. Anthony Hughes - Officer Johnson
Robert Homans - Sergeant
Virginia McMullen - Secretary
James Bush - Jace Taylor
William Bakewell - David Chadwick
